        <dc:description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Accounting and Financial Reporting in Life Insurance Companies&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, Second Edition, explores concepts that non-accountants need to know about accounting. Topics include regulations, financial statements, financial analysis, budgeting, controls, and auditing &amp;ndash; as well as why each of these should matter to you. Customers rely on your company for financial protection. The knowledge you gain in this course can help you understand the role you play in the financial success of your company, and how to do your part to uphold your company&amp;rsquo;s promise to policyowners.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Module 1 will orient you to Accounting and Financial Reporting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chapter 1: Introduction to Accounting and Financial Reporting&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chapter 2: The Accounting Function&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chapter 3: Accounting Principles and Concepts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chapter 4: Financial Statements and Reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</dc:description>
